6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to state government; creating the
Oklahoma Main Street Grant Program Revolving Fund;
8 designating program to be under the Oklahoma
Department of Commerce; directing Department of
9 Commerce to prescribe form; providing requirements to
qualify for grant; directing certain available funds;
10 providing an appropriation; providing an effective
date; and declaring an emergency.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5013.4 of Title 74, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
18 fund for the Oklahoma Department of Commerce to be designated the
19 "Oklahoma Main Street Grant Program Revolving Fund", which shall
20 consist of all monies appropriated, transferred, or otherwise
21 designated to the fund by law. The fund shall be a continuing fund,
22 not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall be under the
23 administration of the Oklahoma Department of Commerce. All monies
24 accruing to the credit of said fund are hereby appropriated and
Req. No. 11610 Page 1

1 shal l be budgeted and expended in accordance with the provisions of
2 subsection B of this section for the purpose of preserving and
3 developing Oklahoma main streets.
4 B. In order to be considered for a grant, a Main Street shall
5 apply to the Oklahoma Department of Commerce. The application shall
6 be on a form prescribed by the Department of Commerce and shall
7 contain such information as may be required by the Department of
8 Commerce to determine if the applicant is qualified.
9 C. Except as otherwise provided by this section, in order to
10 qualify for the grant, the Main Street applying shall be required
11 to:
12 1. Be a designated and qualified Main Street by the Oklahoma
13 Main Street Program; and
14 2. Upon receiving the grant, the Main Street shall contract
15 with the Department of Commerce which will require a submission of
16 proof that the Main Street is still a designated Main Street and an
17 invoice to the Department of Commerce to be paid no earlier than
18 June 1 of any fiscal year in which there are funds to award the
19 grant.
20 D. If an awarded Main Street is no longer a designated Main
21 Street, they will be removed from the grant program and shall be
22 ineligible to receive grant funds. Any funds that are available
23 because of the applicants that were preapproved but are no longer
24
