1 desi gnated Main Streets will be reallocated evenly to the other
2 qualified grant awardees.
3 E. No Main Street that applies for the grant will depend upon
4 future awarded funds for operations, but in any year awarded, funds
5 may go towards any cost associated with their operations.
6 SECTION 2. There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma
7 Department of Commerce from any monies not otherwise appropriated
8 from the General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal
9 year ending June 30, 2026, the sum of Two Million Dollars
10 ($2,000,000.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to supplement
11 the funding for the Oklahoma Main Street Grant Program.
12 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
13 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
14 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
15 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
16 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
17 SECTION 5. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
